        "# **Computational Drug Discovery [Part 1] Download Bioactivity Data**\n",
        "\n",
        "## Project Overview\n",
        "\n",
        "In this Jupyter Notebook, we develop a real-world data science project focused on drug discovery. The goal is to build a machine learning model using bioactivity data obtained from the ChEMBL database.\n",
        "\n",
        "This project demonstrates how computational methods can be applied to predict the biological activity of chemical compounds, enabling more efficient identification of potential drug candidates.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Objectives\n",
        "\n",
        "- Retrieve and preprocess bioactivity data from ChEMBL\n",
        "- Convert molecular structures (SMILES) into numerical features using RDKit\n",
        "- Perform exploratory data analysis (EDA)\n",
        "- Train machine learning models to predict molecular activity (e.g., IC50)\n",
        "- Evaluate model performance using appropriate metrics\n",
        "\n",
        "## Applications\n",
        "\n",
        "This workflow is widely used in:\n",
        "- Drug discovery\n",
        "- QSAR/QSPR modeling\n",
        "- Virtual screening pipelines\n",
        "\n",
        "In this Jupyter notebook, we will be building a real-life **data science project** that you can include in your **data science portfolio**. Particularly, we will be building a machine learning model using the ChEMBL bioactivity data.\n",
        "\n",
        "---"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### **ChEMBL Database**\n",
        "\n",
        "The [*ChEMBL Database*](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/chembl/) is a database that contains curated bioactivity data of more than 2 million compounds. It is compiled from more than 76,000 documents, 1.2 million assays and the data spans 13,000 targets and 1,800 cells and 33,000 indications.\n",
        "[Data as of March 25, 2020; ChEMBL version 26].\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ],
